body_html:
TensorFlow 0.8 is not available for Windows - note that it is actually an older version than TensorFlow 0.12 (the version numbers are not decimal fractions, so 0.80 != 0.8).

The tf.contrib.skflow package has been removed, and that tutorial is out of date. Please contact the author and ask them to update it to the latest APIs.

body:
TensorFlow 0.8 is not available for Windows - note that it is actually an **older** version than TensorFlow 0.12 (the version numbers are not decimal fractions, so 0.80 != 0.8).

The `tf.contrib.skflow` package has been removed, and that tutorial is out of date. Please contact the author and ask them to update it to the latest APIs.
